SM121 (DGX Spark GB10) shared memory fix for cutlass_moe_fp4 / nvfp4_blockwise_moe

Problem:
  SM121 has only 101 KB shared memory per block, while CUTLASS's
  StageCountAutoCarveout computes stage count against the compile-time
  SM-family maximum (228 KB for SM12x). The SM120 kernel path in
  run_fp4_blockwise_scaled_group_mm_sm120() requests ~147 KB SMEM via
  Pingpong schedule + auto stage carveout, which SM121 cannot satisfy.
  Result: nvfp4_blockwise_moe.cuh:78 device-side assert whenever the
  triton or cutlass MoE runner dispatches to cutlass_moe_fp4 for NVFP4.

Fix:
  Force StageCount<1> (single-stage mainloop, no double buffering) and
  switch from KernelPtrArrayTmaWarpSpecializedPingpong to the non-pingpong
  KernelPtrArrayTmaWarpSpecialized schedule. Combined, this cuts mainloop
  SMEM from ~147 KB to ~74 KB and fits the 101 KB SM121 budget.

  The ThreadBlockShape<_128, _128, _128> is unchanged — TMA descriptor
  validation allows stage/schedule changes but rejects M/N reduction.

Equivalent to the tile/stage change in TensorRT-LLM PR #12141
(NVIDIA/TensorRT-LLM, merged 2026-03-18) which applied the same approach
in TRT-LLM's fp4_gemm_template.h for SM121.

Refs:
  - https://github.com/NVIDIA/cutlass/issues/3144 (root cause)
  - https://github.com/NVIDIA/TensorRT-LLM/pull/12141 (reference approach)
  - https://github.com/sgl-project/sglang/pull/20012 (JIT migration: file moved
    from sgl-kernel/csrc/moe/ to python/sglang/jit_kernel/csrc/moe/)

Upstream source: sgl-project/sglang tag v0.5.10

--- a/python/sglang/jit_kernel/csrc/moe/nvfp4_blockwise_moe.cuh
+++ b/python/sglang/jit_kernel/csrc/moe/nvfp4_blockwise_moe.cuh
@@ -289,7 +289,9 @@
   // Architecture definitions
   using ArchTag = cutlass::arch::Sm120;
   using OperatorClass = cutlass::arch::OpClassBlockScaledTensorOp;
-  using StageCountType = cutlass::gemm::collective::StageCountAuto;
+  // SM121 (DGX Spark GB10): only 101 KB SMEM vs 228 KB on SM120.
+  // StageCount<1> halves mainloop SMEM from ~147 KB to ~74 KB.
+  using StageCountType = cutlass::gemm::collective::StageCount<1>;
   using ThreadBlockShape = Shape<_128, _128, _128>;
   // on the tile size

@@ -327,9 +329,8 @@
       ElementAccumulator,
       ThreadBlockShape,
       ClusterShape,
-      cutlass::gemm::collective::StageCountAutoCarveout<static_cast<int>(
-          sizeof(typename CollectiveEpilogue::SharedStorage))>,
-      cutlass::gemm::KernelPtrArrayTmaWarpSpecializedPingpong>::CollectiveOp;
+      StageCountType,
+      cutlass::gemm::KernelPtrArrayTmaWarpSpecialized>::CollectiveOp;

   using GemmKernel = cutlass::gemm::kernel::GemmUniversal<ProblemShape, CollectiveMainloop, CollectiveEpilogue>;

